This ticket should leverage the dimensions filter in Boto's describe_alarms_for_metric() method as documented at http://boto.cloudhackers.com/en/2.3.0/ref/cloudwatch.html#boto.ec2.cloudwatch.CloudWatchConnection.describe_alarms_for_metric

sample call for obtaining an average CPU Utilization threshold alarm via boto...

{code}
dims = {'InstanceId': ['i-123456']}
cpu_alarm = cw_conn.describe_alarms_for_metric('CPUUtilization', 'AWS/EC2', period=300, statistic='Average', dimensions=dims, unit='Percent')
{code}

Dimension keys are described at http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonCloudWatch/latest/DeveloperGuide/ec2-metricscollected.html#ec2-metric-dimensions
